From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 09:46:00 +0800
Subject: Add //purecloak/common:buildflags dependency to content/browser

Add PureCloak buildflag header dependency so that Chromium source files
in content/browser can use BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK) for conditional
compilation of anti-detection patches.

---
 content/browser/BUILD.gn | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/content/browser/BUILD.gn b/content/browser/BUILD.gn
index abcdef1..abcdef2 100644
--- a/content/browser/BUILD.gn
+++ b/content/browser/BUILD.gn
@@ -254,6 +254,7 @@
     "//net",
     "//net:extras",
     "//printing/buildflags",
+    "//purecloak/common:buildflags",
     "//services/audio",
     "//services/audio/public/cpp",
     "//services/audio/public/mojom",
